
= About =
This Page will list the REST API to create/update/delete vTerminal(s) to [[OpenDaylight Virtual Tenant Network (VTN):VTN Coordinator|VTN Coordinator]]
 
= List of Functions Supported =
== Create vTerminal ==
This operation is used to create a VTN.
=== Request ===
 {| class="wikitable"
|-
| Method || POST
|-
| Request URI   || 
/vtns/{vtn_name}/vterminals
|-
| Request Body (XML)  ||
  <vterminal vterminal_name="{vterminal_name}" controller_id="{control
 ler_id}" domain_id="{domain_id}" description="{description}"/>
|-
| Request Body (JSON) ||
 {
    "vterminal": {
        "vterminal_name": "{vterminal_name}",
        "controller_id": "{controller_id}",
        "domain_id": "{domain_id}",
        "description": "{description}"
     }
  }
|}


; Description of Request Elements 
{| class="wikitable"
|-
| Element || Description || Required
|-
|vterminal_name || vTerminal name.
Valid value: Up to 31 characters including
alphanumeric characters and underscore (except at the
beginning).
||Yes
|-
|controller_id || Controller ID.
Valid value: Up to 31 characters including
alphanumeric characters and underscore (except at the
beginning).
||Yes
|-
|domain_id ||Domain ID.
Valid value: Up to 31 characters including
alphanumeric characters and underscore (except at the
beginning), and the string "(DEFAULT)".
Note: "(DEFAULT)" indicates default domain.
||Yes
|-
|description || Additional information.
Valid value: Up to 127 characters.
||No
|}

